=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People put cryptocurrency into a pot.</li>=09<=
li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some smart contract uses the cryptocurrenc=
y in the pot to make a profit, e.g., by lending the cryptocurrency to peopl=
e who want to use or short it, or as capital for=C2=A0automated market maki=
ng.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The people who put their crypt=
ocurrency into the pot share in the profit. Generally the pot pays a yield =
to its investors, either a fixed yield or one based on the returns the smar=
t contract earns.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Also, sometimes,=
=C2=A0the investors get =E2=80=9Cgovernance tokens,=E2=80=9D which loosely =
speaking represent something like equity ownership of the pot, the right to=
 decide how to run the pot, etc.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If y=
ou replace the words =E2=80=9Csmart contract=E2=80=9D in that description w=
ith the word =E2=80=9Cperson=E2=80=9D (or =E2=80=9Ccompany,=E2=80=9D etc.),=
 you have a classic description of an =E2=80=9Cinvestment contract.=E2=80=
=9D Under the =E2=80=9CHowey test=E2=80=9D=C2=A0of=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24693311.258647/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjL=
